
Q. What is less vs sass?

Q. What is less?
Q. What are mixins in less?
	//object oriented 
	
	.roundedCorners(@radius){
	-webkit-border-radius : @radius;
	-moz-border-radius : @radius;
	border-radius : @radius;
	}

	img{
		.roundedCorners(10px)
	}
	
	img{
	-webkit-border-radius : 10px;
	-moz-border-radius : 10px;
	border-radius : 10px;
	}

	.commonRules{
		border : @border;
		text-align : center;
	}
	
	
	header{
		font-size: @fontSize;
		.cooonRules;
	}
Q. What are variables in less?
	@black : #000;
	@fontSize : 12px;
	@padding : 15px;
	@border : 2px solid @black;
	@stringVar : " - on CodePen";
	
	header{
		color : @black;
		font-size : @fontSize;
		padding: @padding  @padding + 15;
	}
	
	footer{
		border : @border
	}
	
	
Q. How we can nest css rules together?
	h1{
		&:after{
			content ; @stringVar;
		}
	}
	
	h1:after{
		content ; @stringVar;
	}
	
	
	a{
		&:hover{
			color : darker(@black,20%);
		}
	}
	
	
	footer{
		p{
			span{
			
			}
		}
	}
	

Q. operators?
	margin : @margin+30
margin : @margin-30
margin : @margin*3
margin : @margin/3


Q. parametrized mixins?
	.roundedCorners(@radius:10px){
	-webkit-border-radius : @radius;
	-moz-border-radius : @radius;
	border-radius : @radius;
	}
Q. guarded mixins?
	.set-text-color (@bg-color) when
	(lightness(@bg-color)>= 50%){
		color:@dark;
		background:@bg-color;
	}
	
	//call
	.set-text-color(@template_color)
	.set-text-color(lightness(@template_color,10%))
	
Q. built-in functions
	lighten()
	darken()
	fadein()
	fadeout()
	fade()
	
Q.partials(@import)
	@import url(https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css)


Q. DRY? Dont repeat yourself..


